									<img title='Soldiers and airmen from the Minnesota National Guard conduct COVID-19 testing at an armory on May 23, 2020.&#13;Linsey Williams/Minnesota National Guard' style='' alt='Soldiers and airmen from the Minnesota National Guard conduct COVID-19 testing at an armory on May 23, 2020.<br>Linsey Williams/Minnesota National Guard' class='' src='/polopoly_fs/1.631541.1590682822!/image/image.jpg_gen/derivatives/660x440/image.jpg' />				
			
		    
						</a>
					</div>
					<div class="small-16 large-7 columns">
													<div class="row">
						<div class="small-16 columns">
															<p>Thousands of troops who have deployed to help battle the coronavirus pandemic could soon receive hazard pay and awards to recognize their service, the military’s top general said Thursday.</p>
